ker and some funky CSS grid-based layouts. The actions grids needed the information to load neatly under each row of 3, but this content was fully dynamic. Javascript was used to insert this data in the right place. With JS turned off the actions just worked as links to the indivual action so the site still functions well &#8211; a nice progressive enhancement.<\/p>\n<p>The home page use Fullpage.js for nice slide by slide full screen presentation with each Lottie animation triggered on slide change. <\/p>\n<p>The pledge system used cookies to remember the uses choice and then some custom WordPress code to insert entries into the pledge table for use with the ticker.<\/p>\n\t\t\t<\/div>\n<\/section>\n\n\n<section class=\"tombo-block tombo-text-block\">\n\t<div class=\"wrapper\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align: center;\">\n<a class=\"button\" href=\"https:\/\/youdoo.today\">View the site<\/a><\/p>\n\t\t\t<\/div>\n<\/section>","protected":false},"featured_media":0,"template":"","class_list":["post-179","work","type-work","status-publish","hentry"],"acf":[],"yoast_head":"<!-- This site is optimized with the Yoast SEO plugin v25.1 - https:\/\/yoast.com\/wordpress\/plugins\/seo\/ -->\n<title>Youdoo Pledge Site - liamnguyen.dev<\/title>\n<meta name=\"description\" content=\"How I build the Bristol environmental actions site with a pledge system and Lottie animations with Bristol&#039;s Oku Design\" \/>\n<meta name=\"robots\" content=\"index, follow, max-snippet:-1, max-image-preview:large, max-video-preview:-1\" \/>\n<link rel=\"canonical\" href=\"https:\/\/liamnguyen.dev\/work\/youdoo-pledge-site\/\" \/>\n<meta property=\"og:locale\" content=\"en_GB\" \/>\n<meta property=\"og:type\" content=\"article\" \/>\n<meta property=\"og:title\" content=\"Youdoo Pledge Site - liamnguyen.dev\" \/>\n<meta property=\"og:description\" content=\"How I build the Bristol environmental actions site with a pledge system and Lottie animations with Bristol&#039;s Oku Design\" \/>\n<meta pro